<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-152-388  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 152 388.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computing Canada  March 2 1989 v15 n5 p35(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Service means much more than repair.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Stanfield, John.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Although it is clear that the third-party service market isflattening out, some companies are experiencing growth in thesector.andP;  Nonetheless, the third-party market is only part of thetotal market.andP;  Customers are beginning to look for a total serviceoffering to respond to problems that are resulting from increaseduse of larger and more complex communication networks, differentvendor equipment and wider use of local area networks.andP;  Some ofthe services that are being offered include network services suchas network design and installation, training and educationservices, start-up services, which help make the start-up of asystem or network more smooth, and complete care services, whichencompass the whole gamut of services offered.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Service IndustrySupport ServicesMaintenanceThird-Party MaintenanceCustomer Relations.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>